				<p>WikiFindings aims to assist in the communication of newly published scientific research to a lay audience, researchers in other fields and the general public.</p>
				<p>The WikiFindings project was conceived by <a href="https://sites.google.com/view/andrewdhigginson/home">Dr Andrew Higginson</a>, a Research Fellow in Theoretical Ecology currently based at the University of Bristol, who is actively developing it in partnership with Red Mars Digital.</p>
				<hr>
				<p>The site is built in <span class="spanTech spanLanguage">Node</span>, <span class="spanTech spanFramework">Express</span> and <span class="spanTech spanDB">mongoDB</span>.</p>
				<p>From a technical standpoint, WikiFindings represents a significant step up in complexity from other projects undertaken to date - requiring multiple user types, detailed database models, asynchronous server events and secure user data handling with dependencies such as <span class="spanTech spanLibrary">Passport</span> and <span class="spanTech spanLibrary">Nodemailer</span>.</p>
				<p>At the time of writing (Sep 2017) WikiFindings is alpha-ready and will shortly be rolled out to a limited trial group for production testing and loading of initial content.</p>

